{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T09:01:12.326Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Running agents inside customer VPCs is the pattern of deploying a self-hosted Claude agent runtime entirely "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"within the customer’s AWS VPC (or equivalent in other clouds)"},{"type":"text","text":", so that the agent’s code, prompts, outputs, and all tool execution stay inside the customer’s own network boundary. In the Managed Agents vs. Self-Hosted comparison, this is why teams choose self-hosted: to meet compliance, data residency, and sovereignty requirements that cloud-hosted managed runtimes cannot satisfy."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Running inside a customer VPC means:\n- The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"agent runtime"},{"type":"text","text":" (orchestrator, workers, API) runs in infrastructure that is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"owned and controlled by the customer"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- All "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"execution"},{"type":"text","text":" (tool calls, code generation, document processing) happens "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"inside the VPC"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- All "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"data"},{"type":"text","text":" (prompts, responses, context, artifacts) stays "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"inside the customer environment"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- The agent may still call external APIs (e.g., Anthropic’s Claude API), but only over "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"controlled network paths"},{"type":"text","text":" (private links, VPC endpoints, or restricted egress)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is different from running a container locally or on a dev machine. It’s a production pattern for regulated environments where:\n- Data cannot leave the organization’s network.\n- Workloads must be auditable and governed by internal policies.\n- Compliance frameworks (HIPAA, SOC 2, ISO 27001, FINRA, etc.) impose strict controls."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why it matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Customers in regulated industries (healthcare, finance, government, legal) often cannot use cloud-hosted managed agent services because:\n- Their data must stay "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"in-region"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"on-prem"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- They must control "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"security boundaries"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"credential management"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"audit logs"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- They need to meet "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"compliance requirements"},{"type":"text","text":" that require workloads to be inside their own VPC."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-hosted agent runtimes in customer VPCs let organizations:\n- Keep "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"prompts and outputs"},{"type":"text","text":" under their own governance.\n- Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"internal tool integrations"},{"type":"text","text":" (databases, APIs, file stores) that are not exposed to the public cloud.\n- Enforce "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"network isolation"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"encryption"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"access controls"},{"type":"text","text":" that match their compliance requirements."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of the VPC as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"private fortress"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- The agent runtime is a building inside that fortress.\n- All operations happen inside the fortress walls.\n- External communication (e.g., Claude API calls) goes through "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"guarded gates"},{"type":"text","text":" (private links or restricted egress).\n- The customer controls the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"permits, guards, and audit logs"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In AWS terms, the agent runtime is deployed as:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"EKS pods"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"EC2 instances"},{"type":"text","text":" inside the VPC.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"RDS"},{"type":"text","text":" or other databases in the same VPC for state and checkpoints.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Private subnets"},{"type":"text","text":" with no public access.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"VPC endpoints"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"PrivateLink"},{"type":"text","text":" for calling external APIs without traversing the public internet."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How it works"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Architecture"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A typical VPC-deployed agent runtime stack:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Component"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Role"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"VPC placement"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"API layer (FastAPI/LangServe)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Exposes run endpoints, status, streaming"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Private subnet, behind internal ALB"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Worker layer (Celery/Kubernetes)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Executes agent loops, tool calls"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Private subnet, with node groups"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Orchestrator (LangGraph/custom)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Manages workflows, checkpoints"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Internal service in VPC"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"State store (Redis/Postgres)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Persistent run state, checkpoints"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Private subnet, with encryption"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Secrets store (Vault/SSM)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Credential management"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Private subnet, with access policies"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Network egress"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"External API calls (e.g., Anthropic)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"VPC endpoints / PrivateLink / NAT with restrictions"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All components run inside the customer VPC, with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"no public access"},{"type":"text","text":" unless explicitly required."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Network isolation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key network controls:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Private subnets"},{"type":"text","text":": No public IP addresses for agent components.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Security groups"},{"type":"text","text":": Restrict inbound/outbound traffic to only required ports and endpoints.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"VPC endpoints/PrivateLink"},{"type":"text","text":": Call external APIs (like Anthropic) over AWS private networking, not public internet.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"NAT gateways with restrictions"},{"type":"text","text":": If public egress is needed, use NAT with strict egress policies.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Network ACLs"},{"type":"text","text":": Additional layer of traffic filtering."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This ensures the agent cannot:\n- Escape the VPC.\n- Access unauthorized services.\n- Exfiltrate data to external networks."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Credential and secret management"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Store credentials in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"AWS Secrets Manager"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"SSM Parameters"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"HashiCorp Vault"},{"type":"text","text":" inside the VPC."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"IAM roles"},{"type":"text","text":" for service-to-service authentication."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Rotate credentials automatically."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"short-lived tokens"},{"type":"text","text":" for API access."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This keeps secrets under the customer’s control, not Anthropic’s."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Data residency and compliance"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"By running inside the VPC:\n- All data (prompts, outputs, context, artifacts) stays "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"in the customer’s VPC"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Data can be "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"encrypted"},{"type":"text","text":" at rest and in transit.\n- Access is governed by "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"IAM policies"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"security groups"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"audit logs"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- The customer can enforce "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"region-specific hosting"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., only US-East, only EU)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This satisfies compliance requirements that data must not leave the organization’s network or region."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-offs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Data stays "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"inside the customer VPC"},{"type":"text","text":", meeting compliance and data residency requirements.\n- Customer controls "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"security boundaries"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"credentials"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"audit trails"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Can integrate with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"internal tools"},{"type":"text","text":" (databases, APIs, file stores) not exposed to the public cloud.\n- Enables "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"regulated industry"},{"type":"text","text":" deployments (healthcare, finance, government)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Trade-offs:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- You must "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"build and maintain"},{"type":"text","text":" the infrastructure (unlike Managed Agents).\n- Requires "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"infrastructure engineering"},{"type":"text","text":" expertise.\n- More "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"complex"},{"type":"text","text":" to deploy and operate.\n- You’re responsible for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"security updates"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"monitoring"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"scaling"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best practices"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy agent runtime in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"private subnets"},{"type":"text","text":" with no public access."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"VPC endpoints/PrivateLink"},{"type":"text","text":" for external API calls."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Store secrets in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"managed secret stores"},{"type":"text","text":" (Vault, SSM, Secrets Manager)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"IAM roles"},{"type":"text","text":" for service authentication."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Enable "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"encryption"},{"type":"text","text":" at rest and in transit."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Set up "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"audit logging"},{"type":"text","text":" for all agent actions."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implement "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"resource limits"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"monitoring"},{"type":"text","text":" for anomalies."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Running agents inside customer VPCs means the entire agent runtime is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"deployed and controlled within the customer’s AWS VPC"},{"type":"text","text":", keeping all data and execution inside the customer boundary."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This pattern is used for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"compliance"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"data residency"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"regulatory requirements"},{"type":"text","text":" that cloud-hosted managed agents cannot satisfy."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key controls: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"private subnets"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"VPC endpoints"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"secret stores"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"IAM roles"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"encryption"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"audit logging"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-hosted VPC deployments give full control but require infrastructure engineering effort."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
